{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "11", "m": "04", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "10", "M": "22", "S": "00"}}, "news": [{"title": "Mangaluru civic body logs record \u20b9149.6 crore property tax collection in FY26", "para": "Mangaluru City Corporation achieved a record Rs 149.6 crore in property tax collection for 2025-26, exceeding its target. This success, driven by physical property inspections in pilot wards and campaigns, will fund development works. The corporation also plans to implement QR codes on advertisements and an online booking platform to enhance revenue.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/mangaluru-city-corporation-achieves-record-1496-crore-property-tax-collection-in-fy26/130187408?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-108238/130187408.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Prayagraj civic body extends property tax relief to new buildings", "para": "Prayagraj Municipal Corporation will offer a 25% tax rebate on the annual rental value for newly constructed residential buildings. This benefit, aimed at providing financial relief and encouraging tax compliance, applies only to self-occupied, purely residential properties. The move aligns with previous demands for tax concessions for older buildings as well.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/prayagraj-municipal-corporation-offers-25-tax-rebate-on-new-residential-buildings/130187381?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-41312/130187381.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Telangana: Despite merger, building approval revenue in CURE sees only marginal rise", "para": "Despite merging municipalities into three corporations, revenue from building approvals in Telangana's Core Urban Region saw only a marginal increase. While the expanded region recorded \u20b91,172 crore in 2025-26, this marks a significant decline from 2022-23. Most approvals now occur outside GHMC limits, with Cyberabad Municipal Corporation contributing the largest revenue share.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/telangana-building-approval-revenue-posts-marginal-increase-post-municipality-merger/130187352?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-32566/130187352.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}